<section xml:id="sec-coordinates_and_graphs" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
   <title>Coordinates and Graphs</title>

   <p>
        <m>\textbf{Coordinates}</m> refer to an ordered pair of numbers (x, y), that represent the exact location of a point on the Cartesian plane.
    </p>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    The <m>\textbf{x-coordinate}</m> tells you how far left or right the point is from the origin.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    The <m>\textbf{y-coordinate}</m> tells you how far up or down the point is from the origin.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

